description:
A bizarre alien spacecraft lands in the middle of Metropolis, even eclipsing the sun at one point. An alien female exits the cockpit, and is confronted by Superman, the Legion of Superheroes and the Metropolis Special Crimes unit, who attempt to speak with her, though they cannot understand her language, and the Legion's translators aren't working.

Saturn Girl enteres her mind, and figures out a way to allow her to speak, with the lights off. A huge group of superheroes listens as she tells the tale of a sun eater coming to their planet. They divide into groups, with Mister Miracle leading the charge against the sun eater.

Miracle and his team arrive near it and start to attempt to use a Boom tube on it. Meanwhile, Phantom Stranger visits the Spectre in an attempt to gain his help, only to fail. After realizing they couldn't boom tube it anywhere as it is in another dimension, the fire users attempt to create a second sun.

That plan works, and the Sun Eater devours it, leaving the fire users burnt out. Still, the Sun Eater then goes for the other sun, and devours it, leaving the entire world in darkness.

At the back of the book, there is a Star file.
name: Dusk

description: In revenge for their murdered friend, Tommy and Natt go the Siamese twin crimelord's house with the plan of simply killing every single person there. It goes well into Johnny Navarone shows up and again badly wounds Tommy. A lucky shot destroys Johnny's hand. Stunned, he doesn't react as Tommy shoots him dead.
name: Ten Thousand Bullets, Part 4

description: The Saint of Killers is born and goes about his terrible business. He curses himself by intentionally murdering innocents.
name: Saint of Killers Part 4

description: B.B. gets a job; Jezebel gets an eviction notice; and the hospitalized Mayor Huxley is in jeopardy once again. Meanwhile, Monty Vickers orchestrates the fight of the century--preparing Kid Gloves to box his way up the evolutionary ladder. Plus, the Missing Link is on the loose!
name: Episode Five

description: The heroes of the DCU's first attempt to stop the Sun-Eater failed! Worse yet, the Earth's greatest hero, Superman, cut off from his power source, is powerless to stop the coming doom! Will the heroes be forced to do the unthinkable and team-up with the arch villain Lex Luthor in order to save mankind from certain extinction?
name: Darker Grows the Night

description:
"The Final Night" tie-in issue! As the sun extinguishes and the end draws near, Tommy, Sean, Natt, Hacken and Ringo all gather in Noonan's Bar for one last drink. They share personal stories from their past during what seems to be their final moments.

With the sun having vanished, Tommy and his friends hole in Noonan's bar and share tales of near-death incidents. Sort of.
name: The Final Night

description: Things get worse. Wide-spread panic and religious hysteria is engulfing the citizens of the world. The heroes are quickly running out of time and even the uber powerful Spectre stands powerless to stave off the inevitable doom. Meanwhile, can the mysterious Phantom Stranger convince Dusk that mankind is worth saving? Story continues in Parallax: Emerald Night (1996) 1-Shot.
name: Keeping Hope Alive

description: Story continued from Parallax: Emerald Night (1996) 1-Shot. The heroes of Earth have failed and mankind is doomed. That is unless one man can find the courage within himself to make the ultimate sacrifice, thus saving his soul. Don't miss this must read tale of redemption that truly illustrates what it means to be a hero.
name: The Final Knight

description:
Overview

The only thing greater than Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER #1 is Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER #2! The second issue of this forward-thinking, ground-breaking series continues the adventures begun last issue. In The Paradoxman, Tristan Caine finds shelter from a terrible future in a dilapidated subway station inhabited by the survivors of a devastating nuclear war. In Young Gods, Heros spends the night before his wedding -- a wedding which will unite some of the most powerful gods of the cosmos -- drinking and brooding. And we all know where that can lead! And finally, in The Freebooters, Aran Ana-Kashan finds the man he has been looking for, the great warrior Axus. But finding Axus was only the first step in Aran's quest -- now he must convince the warrior that he is the only being who can save the world. If you're ready for something new -- if you're ready for the first comic of the next millennium -- you're ready for Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER! Windsor-Smith reinvigorated comics in the 1970s, and he's doing it again in this omnibus of wonder!

OverviewTarzan has the cure to the Tara virus -- the genetic virus that is quickly killing his beloved Jane. But the cure is in his own blood, and there are plenty of monstrosities and evil men who wish to spill that blood before Tarzan can ever get back to his mate!

Nakamura Koji is on his warrior pilgrimage, honing his skill for the day that he can avenge himself on the one who bested him in a duel many years before. But he will never make it to that day unless he can defeat the Surudoi school of swordsmanship, who have ambushed him on this journey. In this fight, however, Koji will not be alone -- he is joined by Usagi Yojimbo.
name: The Withered Field

description: As the cold, dark night falls upon Gotham and the world, Batman must cope with a Man-Bat who is driven over the edge and begins to prey upon humans.
name: Darkest Night of the Man-Bat, Part 1: Predation

description:
In this sequel to the movie Mask of the Phantasm,as Andrea drags the Joker into the sewer preparing her vengeance Batman's words return giving her pause in her quest for vengeance.However she is then separated from the Joker by an explosion,she then decided the man who had murdered her father was dead as she left Gotham City for three years.But on this night she has returned in her Phantasm disguise,as she stops a sniper from shooting Bruce Wayne at the behest of a shadowed figure who shows pleasure that Andrea has returned. While inside Bruce is being interviewed by Summer Gleason for his contributions to Gotham's orphans,however the interview is interrupted by Andrea who informs Bruce during a dance that someone is attempting to kill him.However the two are separated by a smoke blast as Andrea jumps from the window with Bruce returning to Alfred to take him home,but are stopped by Andrea who gets in as they start to return to Wayne Manor only for "Andrea" to reveal she is not who she says she is as she transforms.

The woman then forces Alfred to drive taking the two to her boss,while Bruce begins questioning Kitsune before attempting to fight her. However unarmed and about to be killed he is rescued by Phantasm who drives her away as the three return home.Andrea then tells the story of how she has traveled the world acting as a spy,thief and enforcer to anyone who would pay her,before Bruce tells her that nothing can happen between them again before the two begin a passionate kiss. However Alfred is then knocked out, as Andrea and Bruce are ambushed by armed men as Andrea calls for "Alfred" to call the police only to be knocked out from behind by Kitsune who had taken Alfred as a disguise.Held at gunpoint Bruce jumps from the library window into the ocean below, where he enters the cave through a drainage duct and suits up.He then deduces Andrea was the primary target all along before heading out to rescue her,as a man with a joker like smile awakens Andrea revealing himself to be Arthur Reeves. He then has Kitsune prepare to slit Andrea's throat before Batman arrives defeating Arthur's thugs and Kitsune but is knocked out from behind by Arthur utilizing Phantasm's bladed hand with Arthur then unmasking Batman as Bruce Wayne much to his surprise.

And as Arthur prepares to slit a defenseless Bruce's throat he is saved by Andrea,who despite Bruce's pleas for her to leave vows to end this. In her Phantasm garb once again Arthur dives impaling her and falling from the building only to learn Andrea isn't in the costume hitting the ground and dying. Afterwards the police arrive arresting Kitsune, as Batman tells Gordon he never knew who the person behind the Phantasm mask was before taking off. As Andrea in possession of Kitsune's hologram projector watches him leave from afar ,with tears in her eyes.
name: Shadow of the Phantasm

volume.name: The Batman and Robin Adventures Annual

description: Bane seeks revenge upon crime boss Rupert Thorne. Kidnapping Thorne, Bane intends to execute him in front of the man he respects above all others: Batman!
name: To Live and Die in Gotham City!

description: As "Conspiracy" ends, the Dark Knight--trailing the secret society known as the New Dawn--fights his way through the final level of the conspiracy to avert an assassination...and the fear that even darker forces continue to urge him on.
name: Conspiracy Part 3 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
The dying mermaid cryptically implies to Tim and Leah that she doesn't live on actual water, but the depths of the soul.

Tim misunderstands and thinks she drinks blood, but Leah says that's wrong, and in fact Leah is the one who used to drink blood. Now she just starves herself.

Tim is acting nervous around Leah, but it's more because he's attracted to Leah than being scared of her. Leah goes to sleep in the tent. Tim, after being conflicted, sleeps outside.

Leah has her own conflicts, and succumbs to them. She changes form to look like Molly, and makes out with Tim.

Molly, now that she's eaten Faerie food, is converting to being a mybrid human/Faerie, partially due to her often-referenced innately fey nature. Her clothes, and the ground, burn at her touch.

She decides to visit the castle to talk with Titania, and manages to use magic to convince a bridge and a door to let her enter. She burns the axe of a guard and brazenly marches into the court, confronting Titania. The other guests leave in a hurry.

Molly, now surrounded in flames, tells Titania off, explaining how her trick feels like murder, or rape, stealing away her future and her family, and Tim. Titania is shamed, and tries to show her sympathy, but Molly is ticked off, and flares up at her touch.

Tim, after some minutes of exuberant groping, realizes that it's Leah, not Molly. He's angry at her trick, but also feels true attraction to Leah anyway. Leah is touched and tells how she started off as an angel, before being damned by joining Lucifer. Since then, Tim is the only person who cared about her.

They kiss again, and their conjoining brings down a magical rain, created by Tim as an Opener, which starts the desert to flowering. The mermaid is now cured, and sits in their convertible, now full of life's water.
name: Rites of Passage, Part Four: Shells

description: Final Night crossover. "Pray for the Dawn," a tie-in issue to The Final Night. The world is freezing, thanks to a being called the Sun-Eater, and Linda and Wally argue about just how much the public should know. Flash battles a group of survivalists called The Last Hope Militia.
name: Pray For the Dawn

description: As the planet Earth faces its darkest hour, Green Lantern is forced to battle one of the most dangerous villains in the DCU - the sinister Doctor Light! Story continued in Parallax: Emerald Night (1996) 1-shot.
name: Light in Darkness

description: With the mystery house exposed and ready to be demolished, Constantine tries to help Jack pass on to the afterlife--but instead finds himself trapped in the battle of Dunkirk instead! "In the Line of Fire" part 2.
name: In the Line of Fire, Part Two: Over My Dead Body

description: If you think Bart Allen's real life is racing out of control, wait until you get a load of what he dreams about. See if you can keep pace with fast and furious subconscious mind of Impulse!
name: A Game of Spew

description: In the apparent destruction of New Genesis and Apokolips, the surviving Metron arrives on Earth to learn what he can in order to save the New Gods' future! But in the process, Metron discovers his own part in their destruction!
name: After The Fall

description:
In "Crusaders" part 1 of 6, Cassidy wakes up to find himself the subject of an autopsy at the hands of The Grail! Meanwhile, Jesse Custer and Tulip O'Hare arrive in France to search for their captured friend, unaware of the forces aligned against them--foremost of which is The Saint of Killers.

The Saint of Killers is on Jesse's trail; Jesse and Tulip are in France, preparing to find Cassidy; Starr discovers that the thing he loves most has been ruined for him.
name: Of Things To Come (Crusaders Part 1)

description: Robin, out on his own in a snow storm, reluctantly picked up a partner - Spoiler. They Toyman escaped from prison. Robin and Spoiler took down some looters and saved a woman and child who'd been buried in the snow. Robin attempted to teach Spoiler that all life was important, even if they'd tried to kill her.
name: The Final Night: Iced!

description: "Phantom of the World's Fair" concludes at the 1939 World's Fair, which has become a carnival of horror when a serial killer leaves his mutilated victims strung up on the fair grounds. When a friend of Wesley's becomes the latest victim, the Sandman closes in on the shocking truth behind the killer!
name: Slaughterhouse Fair!
Tales From Limbo (Falling Down To Heaven Epilogue)

description: As the sun dies, the Spectre attempts to comfort Gaea, the spirit of the Earth. Doing so causes him to realize the ramifications of some of the things he has done while fulfilling his mission.
name: Use of Power

description:
In ''Hellquest'' part 1 of 3, Jack presents the dying Mist with a coveted keepsake and mercifully brings the dying villain a moment of happiness. Later, the O'Dares enlist Starman's aid in rescuing the Shade and Matt O'Dare! Featuring stunning spot art by Chris Sprouse!

After his adventure in New York with Wesley Dodds, The Golden-Age Sandman, and Dian Belmont, Jack visits The Mist to return his lost World War I medal. The Mist sees Jack as his lost son, Kyle. In a brief, touching moment, we get to see a heroic side of this arch-villain.

Leaving The Mist to his own world, Jack is found by Hope O'dare. She has some bad news about her brother Matt and The Shade.

An aside; this issue marks a hiatus for James Robinson on the letter column. He has been alternating excerpts from The Shade's journal and answering letters. Because of deadline issues he is turning over the letter column to Tony Harris with issue 26.
name: Sand and Stars, an Epilogue; Hell and Back, a Prologue

description:
In this "Final Night" tie-in issue, Roxy reveals her true feelings for the Teen of Steel. Plus, as the events of Final Night spill over, Superboy and the residents of Hawaii seek warmth near a volcano until a new threat rises from the molten magma to threaten them.

Face with the potential end of the world, Superboy takes time to be with his true love, Tana Moon.
name: Running Hot and Cold!

description: Lex Luthor develops a decoy Superman with powers mimicking those of his arch-rival, and sets him loose to attack the world and sully the real Superman's name. Superman faces impossible odds when he goes power-to-power against the Man of Steel!
name: Men of Steel

description: Mysterious beings have disastrous plans for Earth, drawing Wonder Woman and Mike Schorr beneath the arctic ice to combat them. Featuring the mighty Champion.
name: The Men Who Moved the World

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: The team seems to have their heart's desires. Grunge and Roxy have time to themselves. Caitlin leads a team of adoring heroes. But in such a paradise why is Rainmaker miserable? And other things are slowly going wrong.
name: Lindquist's fault, Part. 1

description: Phil literally explodes all over Niseman and Dragon arrives at the hospital a few minutes too late to witness the birth of his son. Kill-Cat is hospitalized, while Dragon learns the truth about Rapture and Peter Klaptin (who is meanwhile being held captive by a shadowy figure). Dragon then prepares to propose to Rapture, only to discover that his son is dead. In reality, the newborn has been captured by The Covenant of the Sword and was replaced with an artificial "dead" fetus.

When Terry meets with Spawn to plan their mission, he tries to understand his friend's chosen hideout as well as their new-found friendship. When he stumbles onto the worms, Al's reaction confuses even more. Terry and Al carry out their mission to document Wynn's involvement in the arms trade. Upon seeing the evidence, Al sends an explosive message to implicate and endanger Wynn's global network infrastructure.
name: Sabotage

description:
Part of "Heroes Reborn."

Rikki Barnes is a girl.

Falcon is an old man.

Red Skull speaks to a crowd chanting "right on."

Captain America has a little boy uncreatively named Steve Rogers, Jr. and a redhead Sharon Carter as his wife.

Nick Fury and Captain America know each other.
name: Courage

description:
Daredevil broke her heart, Bullseye killed her, and the Hand orchestrated her resurrection — now the beautiful assassin is taking control of her life in her own ongoing title! This landmark issue establishes Elektra's new life, introduces a new cast of characters, and brings back a very old yearning to kill!

Elektra's sensei was badly beaten and tortured but they don't know by who. Then it hit her the one person who hated her most... Bullseye.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverMike Deodato, Jr.1
VarVariant CoverMike Deodato, Jr.2
name: Afraid of the Dark

description:
Beast intervenes as a teacher with Jubilee, Husk, M, Synch as well Penance.

Emma Frost and Banshee banter with Leech in the kitchen, but its Howard the Duck along with Chamber and Skin who are on the road to reflect on Skin's past enmities with Tores and his false death in Los Angeles that leaves some questions for Skin on the past he needed to give up. Beast in the meanwhile learns of another secret of M which may not be mutant in origin.
name: To Live and Die and Molt in L.A.

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Tagline: End of the Line
name: Mystery Train

description: This issue had a variant cover from American Entertainment with Spidey and Mary Jane walking in the park.
name: Revelations, Part 1 of 4: Walking Into Spiderwebs

description: The Voyager enters a ferocious ion storm to help a Talaxian ship in distress in "The Storm." Continued next issue.
name: The Storm
The Battle For the Daily Bugle!

description: Following the aftermath of Onslaught's mayhem, Nate and Threnody go for a walk in the park, Washington Square Park in NY. Nate entertains himself and the crowd, while Sebastian Shaw and Selene discuss mutual problems aka Bastion.
name: Open Cage

description: It’s ClanDestine versus the X-Men in an extra-dimensional battle for the ages!
name: The Destine's Darkest Dream

description: After spending months in the wasteland, Jaeger decides to visit Anvard and check up on Emma Grosvenor and her children. He gets in a scuffle with a Free Market warden for claiming to be a free trader but not looking "indian enough", visits Laveau's Bookstore to sell some artifacts he dug up in the wastes, and later bumps into the warden again in the Little Godsfeast Tavern. A full-fledged brawl breaks out, resulting in the warden, Jaeger and two other men flying out of a sixth-floor window. Kalif, a pirate TV cameraman, drags the half-dead Jaeger to Emma's apartment.
name: Salutation

description: Archangel undergoes an unexpected transformation!
name: A Hope Reborn A Past Reclaimed

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
The Sun-Eater has made the Earth grow cold, and Aquaman is still dealing with the aftermath of the invasion!

Aquaman is dealing with the result of the sun being destroyed by the Sun-Eater during the Final Night, while Aquaman talks with Nuada about her sending home their various allies deeming it best for them to spend the most time with their loved ones. Koryak meanwhile is grappling with his regrets over his actions under Kordax's thrall, while theorizing with Dolphin that he might not be dead as there was no body. While Aquaman ponders over Kordax's theory that the ship's technology is in reality controlling him mentally,but pushes it aside when he realizes his dolphins are in danger because with the water frozen they can no longer breathe.

Aquaman then utilizes the portal to let Porm know he is coming, with Porm being proud that the boy she raised is now her savior but is then confronted by a unseen enemy who points a weapon at the dolphin. Aquaman then tries to use his ship which is unable to function forcing him go to the ship at the heart of Poseidonis, with it's sentience revealing it's love for Aquaman but on being rebuffed begins turning the city against the three causing them to flee. They then arrive where they help the group of dolphins by causing a large opening for them to breathe, he then leaves to find Porm only find her bloodied body above the ice with a lightning bolt brand and her blood having been used to write vengeance in Japanese. Aquaman then swears vengeance on the person who murdered Porm.
name: Twilight
True Lies

description: Stormwatch is called into Tokyo, which is being destroyed by a cluster of siamese triplets with massive psionic power. They learn the culprit behind the whole ordeal is the leader of a cult called Raifu Waaku. Fuji is able to stop him and his reign of terror.
Bullock and Soong find out who the Teddy Bear killer is. Montoya has to fight herself out of her kidnapping. Hendricks finds out who is stealing the office supplies.
name: Mortal Remains

description: More urban madness as shock jock Jerry Delman pours gasoline onto the flames of Pearl-mania, rolling out a merchandising machine and competing with everyone from the man-in-the-street to low-budget movie producers for a piece of Luther's fifteen minutes of fame! "Find the girl and find The Pearl," is Frank's mantra . . . and his obsession begins to match Luther's as his search for Tina very nearly kills her . . . and pulls him into an all-out, bone-crunching confrontation with The Pearl himself. The chaos continues . . . don't miss it!

name: Senza cielo

description: The Blood Guard investigate the murder from the previous issue as Sanctuary prepares their attack.
name: Six: Revelation

deck: The Final Night descends as Gorilla Grodd decides to turn Leesburg's citizens into savage gorilla people.
description:
With the world in darkness, the inner beast emerges from the people of Leesburg in "And No Dawn to Follow the Darkness."

Panic arises when the sun goes out.
name: And No Dawn To Follow The Darkness

description: Detective Dudley Soames was to dispose of Nightwing, but instead let him loose and tipped him off on something to check out. Soames delivered the stolen goods to Minh, while Nightwing caught up with the False Facers again at a train station.
name: Gangland Express

description: A world obsessed with cybernetics is bad enough, but the group has to deal with a personality shift that has brought forth their worst personality traits.
name: Dimensional Shadows

description: Final Night tie-in. Ferro shares his plan to stop the Sun-Eater, while the Legionnaires contemplate returning to their own time.
name: "Heart of Iron".

description: OverviewJane is dying from the mysterious Tara virus. Only Tarzan, her mate, can save her -- he holds the cure in his blood. But there is plenty between Tarzan and home -- namely, monstrosities and the evil Ahrtan, who want to spill Tarzan's blood instead! The final, show-stopping conclusion of Tarzan's conflict with the Ahrtan -- and himself!

They say you can never go home again, but Mad Hettie reveals to Brian that he can return to his own time if he is brave enough to once more dare the realm of Faerie--but as Brian and Hettie discover, entering Faerie is one thing, and leaving it is quite another.
name: The Lost Boy, Part Four

description:
The gritty series by award-winning writer Garth Ennis continues in the new arc "Local Heroes!" In part 1, Tommy buries his friend, but his mourning gets cut short when men from the U.S. government show up with evidence linking him to the Dubelz mansion massacre!

Tommy attends the funeral of his closest child-hood friend while new forces gather against him.
name: Local Hero, Part One

description: Despite L'il Big Lil's threats, Kid Gloves boxes his way up the evolutionary ladder in the fight of the century. Meanwhile, Mayor Huxley's life hangs precariously in the balance; Monty Vickers stares into the business end of a shaky gun barrel; and B.B. and Jezebel check out Terminal City's bar scene.
name: Episode Six

description:
Overview

If you're ready for something new -- if you're ready for the first comic of the next millennium -- you're ready for Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER! Windsor-Smith reinvigorated comics in the 1970s, and he's doing it again in this omnibus of wonder! The revolutionary, monthly, ongoing series continues with Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER #3. Not just one story, time, or place, this groundbreaking series follows three entirely different worlds, showcasing Windsor-Smith's wondrously versatile artistry and storytelling abilities. In Young Gods, skull-cracking Princess Adastra challenges Prince Heros to a duel: if he wins, he fulfills his duty by marrying her sister. But if she wins, they could embark on the most exciting adventure of their lives! In The Paradoxman, Tristan Caine begins to unravel the mystery of the Time Bike and encounters the wrath of Willy the Ape-man. And in The Freebooters, Aran Ana-Kashan eats a "happy" cookie and ends up talking to an evil wizard with a multiple personality! Get ready to get excited about comics all over again -- the STORYTELLER is here!

Usagi, while crossing a snow-covered mountain pass, comes across a little girl and her severely wounded father, the only survivors of a party attacked by bandits. It's rabbit against nature as the ronin attempts to usher them safely through the pass, in a snowstorm, stalked by predatory animals, with the threat of an avalanche literally above their heads!
name: A Promise In The Snow
Angel at War: The Fall of Saint Dumas - Part 1 of 3

story_arc_credits.name: Angel at War: The Fall of Saint Dumas

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Angel at War: The Fall of Saint Dumas

description:
Man-Bat is in the Arctic about to prey upon members of a research expedition while being pursued by three deadly killers with orders to destroy him--assassins who are, in turn, hunted by the Batman.

Man-Bat's frozen body is discovered in a block of ice at the North Pole. A group of scientists inadvertently revives him and he goes on rampage while attempting to recreate the formula for his cure.
name: Darkest Night of the Man-Bat, Part 2: Pursuit

description: The Scarecrow is spreading fear to millions through a television broadcast of the Beat Boys, reuniting one of the most popular bands of all time. But Batman is the only one who even suspects a threat!
name: Knightmare

description: "Clay" part 1! Severely beaten by Clayface, Bruce Wayne finds himself fearing death for the first time. Despite being perhaps the finest human combatant in the world, the Dark Knight finds his skills of little use against a foe with super strength and a body of clay.
name: Clay Part 1 of 2

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: "Presidential Race Chapter One: Circular Logic." Wally distrusts a right-wing presidential candidate, who he saves from an assassin. Explosive tops begin appearing and, naturally, Wally suspects The Top.
name: Circular Logic

description:
In the aftermath of epic events of the "Final Night," Green Lantern and the heroes of the DC Universe mourn the loss of a true hero.

This is the "Hal Jordan Funeral" issue. Writer Ron Marz and artist Darryl Banks assembled an impressive cast of DC's stars to say farewell to Green Lantern Hal Jordan in this memorable issue, available in both a regular news stand and deluxe tombstone edition, and including a second feature by writer John Broome and artist Gil Kane. After the heroes of the present day gathered in an emerald construct church to pay their respects to the life of a hero, Swamp Thing used his mastery of plant life to create a green paradise in the once desolate Coast City. With the added tribute of a green eternal flame from former Green Lantern Alan Scott, and an energy construct sculpture of Hal in his prime by the new Green Lantern Kyle Rayner, Hal's legacy was set to shine for ever.
name: His Light Will Burn Forever

description: Whilst scouting for blackmail victims at an orgy, John Constantine finds himself accidentally summoning up sinister beings--which leads to terrible consequences for an anorexic girl and her abusive father.
name: Day of Wine and Roses

description: When his friends push him to get into something that doesn't involve a video screen, Bart Allen tries the Great American Pastime: baseball. Also in this issue: Bart's first kiss!
name: First Base

description: While Metron seeks the truth behind the destruction of New Genesis and Apokolips, Orion reappears on Earth and is reunited with old friends. Meanwhile, Highfather's Source Elemental, Takion, picks up clues to his creation.
name: Night Of The Falling Sky

description:
Jesse and Tulip take on a Grail hit squad, Cassidy ends up more wretched than ever, and Starr's depravity takes a new, even more vile turn in part 2 of "Crusaders."

Starr calls in experts to deal with two of his most important problems, and finds success with each; Jesse tries to figure out how to keep Tulip out of danger, whether she wants him to or not.
name: Too Much Gun (Crusaders Part 2)

description:
"The most unlikely-looking foes reveal themselves to be the most dangerous." - Alfred Pennyworth

Ulysses Hadrian Armstron, a.k.a. the General, makes his return to the pages of Robin after a short stint in a "youth study center." Not wanting Ulysses to return to his nefarious ways, Robin makes a home vist to warn the General that he is under observation.

A trip to the toy store brings the General face to face with Toyman, fresh from his escape off of Stryker's Island (see Robin #35), whom he idealizes for his army toyline.

Toyman sees an impressionable young boy that he can use for his own plans...namely stealing a rar action figure from the vault of an eccentric toy collector.
name: War Toy Story

description:
Akane is your typical teenage girl...until she swallows the Dragon Jewels and is transported to the Heian period of ancient Japan! There in the capital city, Akane learns that she has been foreordained to lead the people as the Priestess of the Dragon God!

But all is not well. Akram, the head of the Demon Clan, has sworn death and destruction on the capital. So Akane is appointed Eight Guardians to stand by her side as she faces the danger that awaits...
name: Vol. 1

description: "The Blackhawk" part 1! As Hitler and Mussolini forge a "Pact of Steel" in Europe, the Golden Age Sandman finds himself drawn into international intrigue when a brash and passionate young Polish pilot petitions Wesley Dodds and others to finance Resistance efforts overseas. But a string of murders seems to follow this pilot--whom the Sandman will come to know as Blackhawk!
name: The Blackhawk: Act I of IV

description: A group of ghostly Indians conjured up by the American talisman clash with a group of ghostly cowboys created by the National Interest. With the Spectre caught in the middle.
name: Beyond the Grave

description:
Demon Quest: Part Two of Three

Attempting to lure the demonic Merritt out of hiding, Jack Knight uses himself as bait. But even with the help of Opal City's police force, Merritt may prove too formidable a foe even for Starman.

Merrit has gotten word that his poster - the poster he uses to capture souls for a demon - is under guard and will be moved to S.T.A.R. labs in Metropolis two days hence. This is certainly unsettling news.

Jack and the O'dares continue to wait for Merritt to come to them.

He does. Bringing chaos and madness with him.

All hell breaks loose.

Jack goes to Hell.
name: To Hell and Back, Part two

description: Roxy and Superboy talk about what happened last issue. Dubbilex's mental abilities are out of control and not even Superboy may be able to help him. Plus, the reporter from issue #32 reveals that there is more to her than meets the eye.
name: Going Mental

description:
A woman vying for Superman's attention gets her wish when the media mistakenly identifies her as his girlfriend! At first she loves the idea...but she regrets her wish when Metallo steps in and kidnaps her to get back at the Man of Steel!

A new superhero is in town. His name is Superior Man. He is a braggart and a show-off type. Capturing headlines for the first few days, he wants to get Superman out of the way. So he asks Superman to leave Metropolis. Superman is unwilling to leave. So Superior Man gets into a fight with Superman. He is quickly revealed as Metallo. Metallo has been brainwashed by Luthor into working for him. Metallo is so angry that he blasts Superman out of his way and goes after Luthor.

Luthor is getting into a chopper when Metallo intercepts him. He is ready to kill Luthor but does not quite succeed. Superman arrives in a lead-lined suit and removes Metallo's kryptonite heart.

Superman then asks Luthor to stop his mindless attacks on him and try to spend his life more creatively. Luthor is confused but quickly makes up his mind NOT to.
name: Be Careful What You Wish For...

description: Beneath the arctic ice, Wonder Woman and Mike Schorr combat an extraterrestrial menace bent on the destruction of Earth. Plus, after their kiss in last issue, how will Wonder Woman react when she sees the mighty Champion again?
name: The Men Who Moved the World Part Two

description: The Marvel and the DC Universe had merged into an Amalgam of both Universes. A man called Access alone had the key to separate them and to keep the two universes separate.
name: The Crossing!
